  "prompt": "What are the must watch Hollywood movies before you die (count not more than 10)?",
  "response": "Selecting must-watch Hollywood movies is highly subjective and can vary depending on personal tastes. However, here is a list of ten films that are often recommended as classics and influential pieces of cinema:\n\n1. **The Godfather (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this crime drama is considered one of the greatest films of all time.\n2. **Citizen Kane (1941)** - Directed by Orson Welles, this film is renowned for its innovative storytelling and cinematography.\n3. **Schindler's List (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this powerful historical drama focuses on the Holocaust.\n4. **Pulp Fiction (1994)** - Directed by Quentin Tarantino, this film is famous for its nonlinear narrative and memorable dialogues.\n5. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont, this inspiring drama about hope and friendship is a favorite among many viewers.\n6. **Casablanca (1942)** - Directed by Michael Curtiz, this romantic drama set during World War II has become a timeless classic.\n7. **Gone with the Wind (1939)** - Directed by Victor Fleming, this historical romance set against the backdrop of the American Civil War is widely acclaimed.\n8. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope (1977)** - Directed by George Lucas, this iconic space opera redefined the genre and inspired generations.\n9. **One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest (1975)** - Directed by Milo\u0161 Forman, this film is a compelling exploration of institutional life and individual freedom.\n10. **The Dark Knight (2008)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan, this superhero film is praised for its complex characters and gripping storyline.\n\nThese films span various genres and eras, offering a well-rounded perspective on Hollywood cinema.",
